  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6580.19 sitting below the 6594 flip strike in PIN regime, dealers are currently net long gamma and will mechanically buy this dip while selling any rallies back toward the massive 6600 gamma wall (+40.6B). The recent GEX surge combined with the -25%+ gamma decay in the past 5 minutes suggests heavy options flow that's reinforcing the current stabilizing structure around 6580-6600. Key levels: dealers turn into heavy sellers above 6594 flip, with maximum resistance at 6600, while 6550 remains the critical support where dealers flip to buying aggressively.\n\n**Bottom line:** Expect price to get pinned between 6580-6600 with limited breakout potential.",
